Pass 1: constraint spine. Inequality pins to a line, tail becomes slack.

The meters, graph, and tableau were three different pictures of the
same constraint, but nothing tied them together. This pass makes the
constraint the persistent object and every other visual a
transformation of it:

- Formulation card transforms in place when slacks are added. The
  operator morphs from "<=" to "=" and a new "+ s_i" term slides
  into the equation from the right. Slack arrives as a modification
  of the thing the student already built, not a separate concept.

- The two-segment meter moves INLINE under each constraint row.
  Same card, same line — "here is the equation; here is what each
  side looks like physically right now." The standalone meters
  panel is gone.

- On the graph, slacksMode fades the half-plane shading, thickens
  the lines, and re-labels each one as "Cn pinned: = rhs" — the
  visual of "=" collapsing the region to its boundary. The
  perpendicular from the current BFS to each line is now labeled
  "tail s_i = value", which is the same word the student sees
  sliding into the equation on the left.

So: when we pin the line to "=", the origin is still feasible
because we added a tail (the slack variable) that absorbed the
distance. Graph shows the geometric tail; canvas shows the
algebraic tail; meter shows the quantitative tail. Three views of
the same transformation.

